## Spec coverage (key requirements)

The test suite exercises all functional requirements from the main specification:

- **§3 Domain rules**: Target tx (Unspecified/Imbalance-GBP at any path segment), GBP-only, future excluded, transfers separate queue, apply transfer description-only, skip persist/reload — `test_gnucash_loader`, `test_apply_engine`, `test_pipeline`, `test_review`.
- **§6–7 Components & evidence**: GnuCash load/write, candidate filter, email parse/index (min_date from earliest Unspecified/Imbalance-GBP tx), receipt OCR/match, ML prediction, review UI (queue, prev/next, evidence), apply (dry-run, backup, audit, journal, rollback), receipt moved only when amount-compatible — `test_gnucash_loader`, `test_email_pipeline`, `test_receipt_pipeline`, `test_matching`, `test_ml_predictor`, `test_pipeline`, `test_review`, `test_apply_engine`, `test_new_features`.
- **§9–10 Review & write**: One-by-one review, before/after, approve/edit/skip, no write without approval, backup/rollback — `test_review`, `test_apply_engine`, `test_integration`.
- **§15 Acceptance criteria**: All 14 criteria are covered by the above plus `test_integration`, `test_system`, `test_system_scenarios`, `test_cli_flags`.

## Fixtures

- **`tests/conftest.py`**: `SAMPLE_GNUCASH_XML` string constant, `sample_gnucash_path` (gzip), `sample_gnucash_xml_path` (plain XML)
- **`tests/fixtures/emails/`**: 13 synthetic `.eml` files across 4 subdirectories (`bank_online_finance`, `amazon`, `subscriptions`, `utilities`) plus root-level files, modelled on Proton Mail export format
- **Receipt images**: Generated programmatically in test setup using Pillow `ImageDraw`

## Tooling
- Test runner: `pytest >= 8.0`
- Python support: CPython 3.11+
- Optional future plugins:
  - `pytest-cov` for coverage gates
  - `pytest-xdist` for parallelization
  - `hypothesis` for property-based matching/parser tests

## Conventions
- Test file naming: `tests/test_<module>.py`
- Test function naming: `test_<behavior>`
- Use AAA structure (Arrange/Act/Assert).
- Shared fixtures in `tests/conftest.py`.
- Use `tmp_path` for all I/O tests.

